    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Trea Turner** (72.23) anchoring the lineup, serving as our highest-rated asset against Pfaadt. **Trea Turner** benefits immensely from a favorable matchup and a delivery-dependent stolen base opportunity, as Pfaadt\u2019s slow tempo (86% success rate against) allows the Zebras\u2019 speed-first philosophy to thrive. Joining him in the top tier is **Yordan Alvarez** (68.04), whose elite 0.393 xwOBA creates a high floor even against a quality arm like Castillo, alongside **Kyle Schwarber** (65.95), who projects for a strong performance at the top of the order. **Colt Keith** (63.89) also presents a significant value play today; his base projection is boosted by a platoon advantage against Junk and the same stolen base environment that makes him an efficient point-per-dollar play for our roster.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today was benching **Carson Benge** (39.27), who finished just shy of the 40-point \"Below Floor\" threshold. While **Carson Benge** has upside, the combination of a difficult L/L platoon matchup against Lopez and a lower batting order slot pushed him behind **Christian Yelich** and **Josh Smith**. We are also exercising caution with **Christian Yelich** (40.96), whose score is suppressed by a challenging matchup against Griffin; he remains on the starting fringe only because of his projected high-order placement. We are closely monitoring lineup confirmations for **Yordan Alvarez**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Josh Smith**, and **Christian Yelich**. Should any of these players be moved to lower spots in the order, we may need to reconsider our depth, particularly given the risk associated with **Josh Smith** facing a sharp Sheehan and **Christian Yelich** laboring against a tough southpaw.",
